						               													<description>Welcome to Ephios, a technologically advanced city which has been politically divided since the High Governor abdicated. &amp;#10;It is now your turn to take the governance of the city but you will have to gain popularity amongst its inhabitants.&amp;#10;Use your relations with the local political figures and unite the alliances that influence public opinion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 game modes in Ephios: Classical and Campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each mode you will have to be the first player to reach 70% of popularity on the popularity card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The crossroads is the place where the political figures of the city meet, it is symbolized by four face-up cards. There are two types of cards, the inhabitants and the figures, each figure belongs to an alliance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During your turn, you must choose one of the four possible actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Recruit: Purchase a figure from the crossroads by spending your persuasion points&amp;#10;     Debate : Discard a figure from the crossroads to earn 2 persuasion points&amp;#10;     Use : Activate the effect of a figure or an inhabitant, then discard it.&amp;#10;     Unite : Discard 2 figures belonging to the same alliance from your hand to earn popularity. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of your turn, you must complete the crossroads.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A campaign is composed of several quick games, but with card variations depending on how the round ended.&amp;#10;Each campaign is unique and you will learn more about the history of Ephios as you will meet new figures and alliances.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
